						               													<description>The Americans have three basic varieties of troops in D-Day: American. You can field elite paratroopers and rangers, regular troops fresh into battle, or experienced veterans. Each of these has a different play style.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;D-Day: American includes three new missions and a linked campaign.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The D-Day: American book has four warriors: Norman &amp;lsquo;Dutch&amp;rsquo; Cota, Lafayette Poole, James Earl Rudder, Turner Turnbull.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The command cards introduce a new concept, title cards. These cards have the title of a division and a special rule giving the division&amp;rsquo;s flavour. The key is that you can only have one title in your force.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;D-Day: American Book contains Forces for:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Parachute Rifle Company,&amp;#10;     Glider Rifle Company,&amp;#10;     Ranger Company,&amp;#10;     Assault Company,&amp;#10;     Rifle Company,&amp;#10;     Veteran Assault Company,&amp;#10;     Veteran Rifle Company,&amp;#10;     M4 Sherman Tank Company,&amp;#10;     M5 Stuart Tank Company,&amp;#10;     Armored Rifle Company,&amp;#10;     Veteran M4 Sherman Tank Company,&amp;#10;     Veteran M5 Stuart Tank Company,&amp;#10;     Veteran Armored Rifle Company, and&amp;#10;     M10 Tank Destroyer Company.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;mdash;description (extract) from the publisher&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
